servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

> This quesadilla is big on flavor AND ready in just 15 minutes with the help of a few kitchen tricks.

Pat @fully cooked chicken breasts{9%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Thinly slice crosswise into strips.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken, scallion whites, and @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook until chicken is warmed through and scallions are slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wash out pan.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Evenly sprinkle @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} onto one half of each tortilla. Top with chicken filling, then sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for filling over medium heat. Add quesadillas and cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheeses have melted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cut quesadillas into wedges and divide between plates. Sprinkle with scallion greens and drizzle with @?hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon} on the side.